title: Home Blogs
content:
Latest Blogs
July 30, 2020
How to Choose the Right TV Size

Bigger is often equated with better. And although TV screens continue to get thinner and larger—with increasingly higher picture quality—it's important to remember that, depending on the distance you're sitting from them, bigger screens don't always provide the best viewing experience. A larger TV screen can look overwhelming or out of place in a more confined space if you sit too close. Too far, and you lose the immersion that we seek to achieve with a good home theater setup. This blog will look at choosing the perfect TV size for your living space.

Read more
July 22, 2020
Furniture Buying Tips for First Time Homeowners

Buying your first home is one of life's most memorable moments. However, with an expanse of empty rooms, bare floors, and blank walls, decorating your new house may also seem like a daunting task. Luckily, with proper planning and consideration, furnishing a home that matches your needs and personal style can be very fulfilling. Before you even start, however, there are several things you need to consider before you ever set foot in a store or shop online. Here are a few furniture buying tips to help you turn your new house into a home.

Read more
July 22, 2020
Focus on BDI Office Features: Storage and Security

For today's home offices, BDI offers a variety of storage and filing solutions in various sizes, configurations, and finishes. Through thoughtful engineering, we have designed our office cabinets and credenzas to better suit the needs of a modern workspace while offering additional solutions that keep your work files and materials securely stored away yet within easy reach. Here are some innovative storage and security features that come standard in our office solutions.

Read more
July 14, 2020
How to Properly Stock A Home Bar

A properly stocked bar is a must for those who love to entertain, and it doesn't need to break the bank. By assessing your needs each season and before planned gatherings, you can start with the basics and build from there. Planning the bar of your dreams can also be a lot of fun. To help you along in this effort, we have prepared the following guide of essential bar supplies that you should always have on hand to help cement your role as 'host extraordinaire' at your next get-together or party.
